
@startuml
skinparam linetype zigzag

class Song {
  -title: String
  -year: Integer
  -length: Integer
  -genre: String
  -trackNumber: Integer
  +getDetails(): String
}

class Artist {
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -websiteURL: String
  +getName(): String
}

class User {
  -id: Integer
  -name: String
  -address: String
  +getId(): Integer
  +getName(): String
  +getAddress(): String
}

class RegularUser <|-- User {
}

class BusinessUser <|-- User {
  -vatNumber: String
  +getVatNumber(): String
}

class Album {
  -title: String
  -trackList: List<Song>
  +getTitle(): String
  +addTrack(song: Song): void
}

class Single {
  -title: String
  -artist: Artist
  +getTitle(): String
  +getArtist(): Artist
}

class Hit {
  -title: String
  -artist: Artist
  -trackNumber: Integer
  +getTitle(): String
  +getArtist(): Artist
  +getTrackNumber(): Integer
}

Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongs to
User "1" -- "0..*" Song : owns
BusinessUser "1" -- "0..*" Single : uploads
BusinessUser "1" -- "0..*" Hit : uploads
Album "1" -- "0..*" Hit : contains
RegularUser "1" -- "0..*" Album : owns
RegularUser "1" -- "0..*" Single : buys
@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **Song** has attributes like title, year, length, and genre. It also has a `trackNumber` if it's part of an album.
- **Artist** has name (unique), date of birth, and a website URL.
- **User** is the base class with `id`, `name`, and `address`.
- **RegularUser** and **BusinessUser** are subclasses of `User`. A user can switch roles depending on context.
- **BusinessUser** has a VAT number and can upload songs as either **Single** or **Hit**.
- **Single** is a song that can be bought directly by regular users.
- **Hit** is a song that can be part of an **Album**, which is composed of multiple hits. Each hit has a track number.
- **Album** maintains a list of hits in order.

